    • Method Detail

      • update

        private void update(Test t)
        this method is used to update the ProblemState. this method get the final results from t and determine if the state of the corresponding problem should be updated or not. if the state of the corresponding problem is 1, then it remain as it is. if the state of the corresponding problem is 0 and all the test cases passed by the program corresponding to the t then the state of the problem will be updated with 1. this method can be executed in parallel to support live platforms.
        Parameters:
        t - object of Test for with update operation perform.

      • getPrograms

        private java.util.List<? extends IntProgramState> getPrograms()
        this method read and return all the program from default program directory. this method internally call ProgramDetails.readProgramDetail() to get problem definition. this process create the new objects of type ProblemState using the objects of type IntProgramState.
        Returns:
        unmodifiable list of IntProgramStates.

      • execute

        public IntLiveResultSet execute(long pid,
                                java.lang.String cmd)
        this method executes the command cmd with proper inputs corresponding to the Program ID specified by pid. this method internally execute the command with all available inputs corresponds to the Program Id available in the default source directory. this method returns live result set immediately and start the processing in parallel. this will method update the resultSet in parallel, after returning.
        Specified by:
        execute in interface IntUserFlow
        Parameters:
        pid - program ID corresponds to the executable command
        cmd - executable command
        Returns:
        object of type IntLiveResultSet.
